                    </div>
              
              
                
              
              
              
                
                    <div class="widget widget_tweet"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">By setting up war on terror as struggle of West vs Islam, Trump does what ISIS wants. <a href="https://t.co/25Qc293zRp">https://t.co/25Qc293zRp</a></p>— Max Boot (@MaxBoot) <a href="https://twitter.com/MaxBoot/status/707792057310580738">March 10, 2016</a></blockquote> <script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div>
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
              
              
              
                    <p> He added: &quot;And we can't allow people coming into this country who have this hatred of the United States.&quot; </p>
                
              
              
              
                    <p> In December, the real-estate mogul triggered uproar when he called for <a href="http://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/arab-billionaire-trump-im-sorry-i-ever-supported-you-n476186">a &quot;complete shutdown&quot; of Muslims entering the country</a>. </p>
                
              
              
              
                
              
